sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant fe@{ "type": "boundary" } as Frontend
    participant rl@{ "type": "control" } as RateLimiter (100 / 15 min)
    participant API@{ "type": "control" } as API
    participant db@{ "type": "database" } as Database
    participant mq@{ "type": "queue" } as RabbitMQ
    participant mw@{ "type": "control" } as MailWorker
    participant smtp@{ "type": "boundary" } as SMTP Server

    Note over User,smtp: Phase 1 — Request reset link

    User->>+fe: Submit email on "Forgot password"
    fe->>+rl: POST /auth/forgot-password
    rl->>rl: Check window/limit

    alt Limit exceeded
        rl-->>fe: 429 Too Many Requests
        fe-->>User: "Too many request!"
    else Within limit
        rl->>+API: Forward request
        API->>API: Generate raw token (32 bytes hex)
        API->>+db: findUnique(user by email)
        db-->>-API: user or null

        Note right of API: Always respond 200 to avoid<br/>email enumeration

        alt User exists
            API->>+db: deleteMany(passwordResetToken by userId)
            db-->>-API: Deleted prior tokens
            API->>+db: passwordResetToken.create(<br/>userId, sha256(token), expiredAt = +1h)
            db-->>-API: Saved
            API->>+mq: sendToEmailQueue(reset link with raw token)
            mq-->>-API: Enqueued
        end

        API-->>-rl: 200 generic message
        rl-->>-fe: 200 "If your email is in our system..."
        fe-->>User: Show neutral success message
    end

    Note over mw,smtp: MailWorker delivers reset email (async)
    mw->>+mq: consume(email_queue_task)
    mq-->>-mw: reset email message
    mw->>+smtp: transporter.sendMail()
    smtp-->>-mw: 250 OK

    Note over User,db: Phase 2 — Submit new password

    User->>+fe: Click link → enter new password
    fe->>+API: POST /auth/reset-password (token, password)

    alt Missing fields
        API-->>fe: 400 "Mising required fields."
        fe-->>User: Show error
    else Has fields
        API->>API: hashedToken = sha256(token)
        API->>+db: passwordResetToken.findUnique(token = hashed)
        db-->>-API: record or null

        alt Token invalid
            API-->>fe: 400 "Token is invalid."
            fe-->>User: Show error
        else Token expired
            API->>+db: passwordResetToken.delete(token)
            db-->>-API: Removed
            API-->>fe: 400 "Token is expired."
            fe-->>User: Show error
        else Token valid
            API->>+db: user.findUnique(id = record.userId)
            db-->>-API: user or null

            alt User missing
                API-->>fe: 404 "User not found."
            else User found
                API->>API: bcrypt.hash(newPassword, 10)
                API->>+db: user.update(password = hash)
                db-->>-API: Updated
                API->>+db: deleteMany(passwordResetToken by userId)
                db-->>-API: All tokens removed
                API-->>fe: 200 "Password changed successfully"
                fe-->>-User: Redirect to login
            end
        end
    end
